## üö© Flag 5 ‚Äì Sensitive Bonus-Related File Exposure

### üéØ Objective
Identify the first sensitive year-end bonus-related file accessed during exploratory activity.

### üßæ Summary
This step scopes analysis to the compromised endpoint **sys1-dept** and user **5y51-d3p7**, then hunts file telemetry for early indicators of bonus/compensation discovery activity. Results are sorted chronologically to identify the first instance of bonus-related data exposure.

‚úÖ Finding  
The first sensitive year-end bonus-related file accessed during exploration was:  
FileName: **BonusMatrix_Draft_v3.xlsx**

The presence of a **Recent Files shortcut artifact** confirms the file was opened or reviewed by the user, indicating exposure of confidential bonus data.

### üîç KQL Query Used
```kql
DeviceFileEvents
| where DeviceName == "sys1-dept"
| where InitiatingProcessAccountName == "5y51-d3p7"
| where FileName contains "bonus"
   or FileName contains "pay"
   or FileName contains "comp"
   or FileName contains "review"
   or FileName contains "performance"
   or FolderPath contains "HR"
   or FolderPath contains "CorpHR"
| project Timestamp, ActionType, FileName, FolderPath,
          InitiatingProcessAccountName, InitiatingProcessFileName
| order by Timestamp asc
